```java
public class PowerOfThree {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        if (n <= 0) {
            return false;
        }
        while (n % 3 == 0) {
            n = n / 3;
        }
        return n == 1;
    }
}
```

This solution uses a while loop to continuously divide the number by 3 as long as it's divisible by 3. If the number becomes 1, it means it's a power of three. If it becomes something other than 1, it means it's not a power of three.

